14/10/2004
SIBENIK, Croatia -- Representatives of the armed forces of the Adriatic Charter signatories -- Macedonia, Albania and Croatia -- participated in a multinational naval exercise on Wednesday (13 October), along with a US destroyer.
The exercise tested their response to a hypothetical surprise terrorist attack on a ship.
The exercise's commander, Captain Marin Stocic, said it was very successful.
(HINA, SRNA - 13/10/04)
